{"name":"Deliverance Light Crossbow","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Manufactured in small quantities across a number of Askellian feudal worlds, the Deliverance is a peculiar weapon that sacriices the punch of regular crossbows for a faster reload time. Usable in one hand or even as a wrist-mount, the Deliverance is a quiet and easily-concealed weapon. If given a forearm weapon mounting, the Deliverance&rsquo;s range is not reduced. Tests to ind a concealed Deliverance sufer a &ndash;20 penalty, and it counts as having a built-in silencer (see page 164 of the DARK HERESY Core Rulebook).&nbsp;</p>","availability":"rare","weight":1,"class":"pistol","type":"","range":15,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10","damageType":"rending","penetration":"0","clip":{"max":1,"value":1},"reload":"half","special":"Primitive (7)","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Range/crossbow.svg","effects":[],"_id":"3HUjzcpJvi9CBuUz"}
{"name":"Snapper Repeating Rifle","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Found only on a few Askellian worlds, the Snapper Repeating Rile represents the pinnacle of black powder engineering. Functionally similar to a musket, the Snapper features a rotating cylinder that holds eight individual shots to lessen the need for reloading. If a Snapper&rsquo;s wielder uses it as an improvised melee weapon and scores two or more degrees of failure on the Weapon Skill test, its mechanisms snap and it is damaged.</p>","availability":"very-rare","weight":45,"class":"basic","type":"","range":50,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":2,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+3","damageType":"impact","penetration":"0","clip":{"max":8,"value":8},"reload":"2 Full","special":"Inaccurate, Overheats, Primitive (8), Unreliable","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Range/winchester-rifle.svg","effects":[],"_id":"3R93v5U2vWfoCRQb"}
{"name":"Musket","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>An improvement on the arquebus, the musket sufers fewer drawbacks with recoil and reload, making it an ideal weapon for ranks of feudal soldiers. A musket counts as a staf when used in melee combat.</p>","availability":"common","weight":7,"class":"basic","type":"","range":30,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+3","damageType":"impact","penetration":"0","clip":{"max":1,"value":1},"reload":"2 Full","special":"Inaccurate, Primitive (8), Unreliable","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Range/musket.svg","effects":[],"_id":"47fyoH1ts8V1z6Ib"}
{"name":"Crossbow","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Crossbows are more compact than regular bows, but require additional mechanical fittings and usually have a shorter range.</p>","availability":"common","weight":3,"class":"basic","type":"","range":30,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10","damageType":"rending","penetration":"0","clip":{"max":1,"value":1},"reload":"2 Full","special":"Primitiv (7)","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Range/crossbow.svg","effects":[],"_id":"CmMghzerAbNreTmY"}
{"name":"Bow","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Though bows come in a multitude of shapes and are made from a wide variety of materials, their basic form and function has changed little throughout the millennia. Even where the Mechanicum may be ascendant, a well-placed and silent arrow can be just as effective as a revered boltgun. A bow always requires both hands to use.</p>","availability":"common","weight":2,"class":"basic","type":"","range":30,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10","damageType":"rending","penetration":"0","clip":{"max":1,"value":1},"reload":"Half","special":"Primitiv (6), Reliable","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Range/bow-arrow.svg","effects":[],"_id":"NjExbge9KajyPWeh"}
{"name":"Arquebus","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>A weapon that exempliies the brute force approach of most black powder weapons, the arquebus is the most common firearm found on Askellian feudal worlds. It can knock a man in full plate of his feet with a single shot, but the recoil, smoke, and reload time make the weapon impractical in the heat of melee fighting. If a character with a Strength bonus of 3 or less uses this weapon, it counts as a Heavy weapon instead of Basic weapon. When fired, an arquebus also creates a cloud with the Smoke (1) quality centred on the firer that lasts for 1d5-1 rounds.</p>","availability":"common","weight":8,"class":"basic","type":"","range":45,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"2d10","damageType":"impact","penetration":"2","clip":{"max":1,"value":1},"reload":"2 Full","special":"Concussive (1),  Inaccurate, Unreliable","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Range/musket.svg","effects":[],"_id":"a4HPHibVMirfnRf2"}
{"name":"Bolas","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>An ancient weapon often seen with hive city bounty hunters and feral worlders alike, bolas have swirling weights at the ends of ropes or wires to entangle a target and often knock him to the ground. Once wrapped up, the foe is easily dispatched or further bound for transport and delivery.</p>","availability":"average","weight":0,"class":"thrown","type":"","range":10,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"","damageType":"impact","penetration":"0","clip":{"max":1,"value":1},"reload":"","special":"Inaccurate, Snare (1)","attack":1.5},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Range/bolas.svg","effects":[],"_id":"aT6OoYpxKGHesTCC"}
{"name":"Longflame","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>The Longlame is a primitive rocket launcher capable of sending a single warhead a signiicant distance, but without a great deal of accuracy. The heavy warhead explodes with considerable force, and leaves a lasting inferno to disrupt enemy movement. This rocket is a single use item and cannot be reloaded.</p>","availability":"rare","weight":6,"class":"heavy","type":"","range":200,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10","damageType":"rending","penetration":"0","clip":{"max":1,"value":1},"reload":"","special":"Blast (4), Flame, Inaccurate,  Primitive (8)","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Range/missile-launcher.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ehH7xGVqWCgbBmmk"}
{"name":"Castigator Heavy Crossbow","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Something of an oddity for a forge world with a reputation for advanced technology, this ostentatious device ires bolts almost a full metre in length and can put a man on the ground with even a glancing hit. Whenever a Castigator inlicts damage (after reductions for Armour and Toughness bonus) on a target that has the Size trait with a value of 5 or lower, that target is knocked Prone.&nbsp;</p>","availability":"scarce","weight":12,"class":"heavy","type":"","range":70,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+6","damageType":"impact","penetration":"1","clip":{"max":14,"value":14},"reload":"2 Full","special":"Concussive (2),  Reliable","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Range/crossbow.svg","effects":[],"_id":"lPRmJX2QBlvhdSIC"}
{"name":"Flintlock Pistol","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Exceptionally basic in both construction and operation, lintlocks are surprisingly common throughout the Imperium due the level of prestige attached to them. Finely-crafted lintlocks pass through Askellian generations as heirlooms, and some fetch enormous prices among high nobles and Rogue Traders alike. This pistol counts as a truncheon when used in melee combat.</p>","availability":"common","weight":3,"class":"pistol","type":"","range":15,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+2","damageType":"impact","penetration":"0","clip":{"max":1,"value":1},"reload":"2 Full","special":"Inaccurate, Primitive (8), Unreliable","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Range/blunderbuss.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ojs98VStRUDTGsmv"}
{"name":"Drakeâ€™s Claw","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>This primitive rocket fires a thin-shelled warhead, and is named for the Rogue Trader who scofed at its outlandish appearance. The direct damage is minimal, but as Drake discovered, the payload breaks into viciously lethal splinters that are horrific to remove. This rocket is a single use item and cannot be reloaded.</p>","availability":"rare","weight":6,"class":"heavy","type":"","range":200,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+2","damageType":"explosive","penetration":"2","clip":{"max":1,"value":1},"reload":"","special":"Blast (3), Crippling (1), Inaccurate, Primitive (7), Tearing","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Range/submarine-missile.svg","effects":[],"_id":"y00UaYsMsrtJ3PEF"}
